 :tx/rationale "ARCHITECTURAL: The storage package is a critical coupling hub — imported by 83 other files across the codebase, nearly every non-trivial package depends on it. The events package is second at 30 imports. This creates a strong architectural bottleneck: any change to storage/models.go or storage/queries.go cascades across almost every package. The storage package also passes raw *sql.DB pointers everywhere rather than using interfaces, making it impossible to test packages independently without a real SQLite database. This tight coupling to concrete SQL types is the single largest architectural weakness — it prevents unit testing without integration infrastructure and makes the transition to any other storage backend (like braid's datom store) a total rewrite rather than an adapter swap."
